1
00:00:07,625 --> 00:00:09,025
‎SAY NO TO PIRACY, SUPPORT ORIGINALS

2
00:01:36,905 --> 00:01:43,025
‎ADAPTED FROM XI XING’S NOVEL
<i>‎QUEEN CHU</i>‎ ON QIDIAN.COM

3
00:02:00,665 --> 00:02:02,145
<i>Dispatch Rider's Tally.</i>

4
00:02:20,105 --> 00:02:22,625
This is how the frontier troops
tie their prisoners.

5
00:02:23,785 --> 00:02:26,625
Could it be betrayal from within?

6
00:02:30,625 --> 00:02:31,905
We're dispatch riders from Wangcheng.

7
00:02:31,985 --> 00:02:35,065
The bandits changed into our uniforms
and went to Beicao Post House.

8
00:02:37,105 --> 00:02:39,905
<i>That post house leads directly</i>
<i>to Yunzhong Prefecture.</i>

9
00:02:45,105 --> 00:02:48,465
Judging by your grace and bearing,
you are no ordinary commoner.

10
00:02:48,545 --> 00:02:50,225
How did you end up in this plight?

11
00:02:51,505 --> 00:02:55,425
My mother dotes on me
and wants me to look refined

12
00:02:56,025 --> 00:02:57,385
so that I might be treated
with more respect

13
00:02:58,225 --> 00:02:59,745
once I marry into another family.

14
00:03:01,825 --> 00:03:03,265
The wilderness is no place

15
00:03:04,105 --> 00:03:05,705
for a lady to wander.

16
00:03:09,585 --> 00:03:10,745
If we were to encounter bandits,

17
00:03:11,345 --> 00:03:13,425
the dispatches you carry
are worth far more than I am.

18
00:03:13,945 --> 00:03:16,385
The roads are rough at night,
and you're out here alone.

19
00:03:17,065 --> 00:03:18,425
If you cross paths with the outlaws,

20
00:03:18,945 --> 00:03:21,905
you will find yourself
completely left to your fate.

21
00:03:23,025 --> 00:03:24,985
If something actually happens to you,

22
00:03:25,825 --> 00:03:27,265
it'll be too late to wish you hadn't.

23
00:03:28,625 --> 00:03:32,905
You are a woman as well,
so if you are not afraid, why should I be?

24
00:03:39,145 --> 00:03:41,465
<i>When you speak,</i>
<i>there is no prominence in your throat,</i>

25
00:03:42,385 --> 00:03:43,985
<i>and the angle of your radius is smooth.</i>

26
00:03:44,825 --> 00:03:47,105
<i>The pauldrons of your chainmail</i>
<i>hang three cun lower than they should,</i>

27
00:03:47,185 --> 00:03:49,425
<i>which means your shoulders are narrower</i>
<i>than those of a typical male soldier.</i>

28
00:03:50,465 --> 00:03:52,185
<i>Your knees tuck inward,</i>

29
00:03:52,265 --> 00:03:53,705
<i>and when you get off a horse,</i>
<i>your toes touch the ground first,</i>

30
00:03:53,785 --> 00:03:54,905
<i>rather than the soles of your feet.</i>

31
00:03:55,425 --> 00:03:58,225
<i>It's an ingrained instinct or a woman</i>
<i>to lift her hem to shun the dirt.</i>

32
00:03:59,785 --> 00:04:02,905
Your flaw lies not in your disguise
but in your habits.

33
00:04:03,545 --> 00:04:05,905
Ma'am, your disguise is flawless,

34
00:04:05,985 --> 00:04:09,105
but your old habits can't be faked.

35
00:04:10,305 --> 00:04:12,385
You knew all along
we weren't dispatch riders?

36
00:04:13,305 --> 00:04:14,985
I grew up in the army.

37
00:04:15,505 --> 00:04:16,985
No one knows soldiers better than I do.

38
00:04:18,184 --> 00:04:19,145
Moreover,

39
00:04:19,865 --> 00:04:22,745
you don't act like dispatch riders,

40
00:04:23,505 --> 00:04:24,545
but more like bandits.

41
00:04:26,385 --> 00:04:30,465
Since you have already seen through us,
why did you still choose to come along?

42
00:04:31,345 --> 00:04:33,305
Aren't you doing the same thing?

43
00:04:34,625 --> 00:04:37,625
Her vow of "My life is worth it"
still exposed us.

44
00:04:37,705 --> 00:04:41,105
You saw through me long ago,
yet you still let me follow you…

45
00:04:42,745 --> 00:04:44,225
because you wanted something from me.

46
00:04:54,665 --> 00:04:56,425
You're sharp.

47
00:04:56,505 --> 00:04:57,825
But it's a pity.

48
00:04:58,545 --> 00:05:01,465
The sharp ones never live long.

49
00:05:06,385 --> 00:05:07,265
What?

50
00:05:08,145 --> 00:05:09,305
Are you trying to take my life?

51
00:05:10,185 --> 00:05:11,265
At the post house,

52
00:05:12,345 --> 00:05:14,585
I saw right through the charade
you and that woman staged.

53
00:05:14,665 --> 00:05:16,025
Yet I brought you along anyway

54
00:05:16,625 --> 00:05:22,505
to see exactly what you hoped to gain
from such an elaborate ruse.

55
00:05:35,705 --> 00:05:36,545
Put down your blade.

56
00:05:40,025 --> 00:05:42,825
I said, put it down.

57
00:05:45,665 --> 00:05:46,865
Jiu.

58
00:05:48,185 --> 00:05:49,305
Who exactly are you?

59
00:05:52,505 --> 00:05:55,665
You posed as dispatch riders
to intercept intelligence

60
00:05:56,185 --> 00:05:57,145
concerning the Northern Desert.

61
00:05:58,545 --> 00:06:00,545
Chu Ling, the Guard General,
has always been invincible.

62
00:06:00,625 --> 00:06:03,025
It's impossible for a Northern Desert
squad to have exploited such a gap

63
00:06:03,105 --> 00:06:05,545
unless someone leaked the dispatch.

64
00:06:06,785 --> 00:06:07,825
How do you know that?

65
00:06:08,705 --> 00:06:10,265
But if you are not closely related,

66
00:06:10,985 --> 00:06:12,305
why go to such lengths?

67
00:06:15,265 --> 00:06:16,545
Unless…

68
00:06:18,305 --> 00:06:19,305
you are from the Northern Desert.

69
00:06:20,025 --> 00:06:23,665
They could never have crossed
Yunzhong Prefecture.

70
00:06:27,825 --> 00:06:29,185
We are from Cangmu Stronghold.

71
00:06:36,905 --> 00:06:40,185
We also suspected
that someone leaked the dispatch.

72
00:06:40,705 --> 00:06:42,105
That is why we targeted
the dispatch riders.

73
00:06:42,705 --> 00:06:45,665
We wanted to find out who at court

74
00:06:45,745 --> 00:06:48,705
is colluding with the Northern Desert
to threaten Yunzhong Prefecture.

75
00:06:48,785 --> 00:06:50,145
Cangmu Stronghold
has always been a mystery,

76
00:06:50,225 --> 00:06:51,345
known to but a few.

77
00:06:52,145 --> 00:06:54,585
Moreover, you never meddle
in the affairs of the court.

78
00:06:55,705 --> 00:06:57,105
Why start interfering now?

79
00:06:57,905 --> 00:06:59,905
I heard during General Chu's campaign
against bandits,

80
00:06:59,985 --> 00:07:03,025
he killed your former leader, Mu Mianhong.

81
00:07:03,105 --> 00:07:03,945
Shouldn't you resent him?

82
00:07:04,545 --> 00:07:05,545
Why help him now?

83
00:07:06,465 --> 00:07:08,185
We may be nothing more than bandits,

84
00:07:09,225 --> 00:07:13,065
but we do know the nation comes
before personal grudges.

85
00:07:13,985 --> 00:07:16,345
General Chu has guarded
Yunzhong for 20 years,

86
00:07:16,945 --> 00:07:18,265
keeping the State of Chu in peace.

87
00:07:19,305 --> 00:07:21,305
If someone in the court

88
00:07:21,385 --> 00:07:24,225
colludes with the Northern Desert
to frame him,

89
00:07:24,305 --> 00:07:25,145
the country will be in peril.

90
00:07:26,465 --> 00:07:28,385
As will Cangmu Stronghold.

91
00:07:34,705 --> 00:07:37,345
To be honest, I am Chu Ling's daughter.

92
00:07:39,385 --> 00:07:42,185
I heard my father was gravely ill
and was rushing to Yunzhong Prefecture.

93
00:07:43,025 --> 00:07:44,865
I encountered some trouble on the road.

94
00:07:45,385 --> 00:07:48,145
I had no choice but to disguise myself
and join the dispatch riders.

95
00:07:54,465 --> 00:07:56,825
If you two are in trouble
and need a place to hide,

96
00:07:58,785 --> 00:08:00,305
would you like to follow me back
to the Stronghold?

97
00:08:10,905 --> 00:08:14,105
Sir, just stopping for a quick bite
or a night's stay?

98
00:08:14,705 --> 00:08:16,465
Have you seen any women
bound for Yunzhong Prefecture today?

99
00:08:16,545 --> 00:08:19,185
There have been plenty of caravans
and women as well.

100
00:08:19,705 --> 00:08:21,225
Which one are you referring to, exactly?

101
00:08:27,545 --> 00:08:30,145
A runaway maid who stole from her master.

102
00:08:30,945 --> 00:08:33,024
She is fair and tender,
bearing no mark of toil.

103
00:08:33,105 --> 00:08:35,825
Few maids dare travel this desolate trail.

104
00:08:35,904 --> 00:08:38,144
Let alone a soft-skinned lady like that.

105
00:08:41,784 --> 00:08:43,784
-Never seen one.
-Liar.

106
00:08:44,345 --> 00:08:45,185
-You've seen her.
-Officer, please calm down!

107
00:08:45,265 --> 00:08:46,745
Where is she?

108
00:08:47,265 --> 00:08:48,425
Let me think.

109
00:08:50,145 --> 00:08:51,705
I remember now. There was such a girl.

110
00:08:51,785 --> 00:08:53,265
She stayed here a couple of days ago,

111
00:08:53,345 --> 00:08:55,465
claiming she was visiting kin
in Yunzhong Prefecture.

112
00:08:55,545 --> 00:08:57,425
Later, she left with the dispatch riders.

113
00:08:57,505 --> 00:08:58,945
I don't know where she went after that.

114
00:09:00,425 --> 00:09:02,105
But I do know where her mother is.

115
00:09:02,865 --> 00:09:04,185
-Her mother?
-Yes.

116
00:09:04,265 --> 00:09:06,905
Her mother hired a carriage
and went back to the village herself.

117
00:09:07,625 --> 00:09:09,345
From that livery stable
three li north of here.

118
00:09:22,185 --> 00:09:23,945
-Come back!
-No, I won't…

119
00:09:24,025 --> 00:09:25,145
-Officer.
-Despicable wretch!

120
00:09:25,225 --> 00:09:26,425
You owe me a fortune!

121
00:09:26,505 --> 00:09:27,545
You…!

122
00:09:31,865 --> 00:09:34,665
A few days ago,
did a girl named Fu come through here?

123
00:09:35,345 --> 00:09:37,225
Officer, what do you mean?

124
00:09:37,305 --> 00:09:40,785
We get so many girls passing through,
how could I remember every name?

125
00:09:40,865 --> 00:09:41,905
Don't play dumb.

126
00:09:42,985 --> 00:09:46,345
She paid you to put on an act
and then left with the dispatch riders,

127
00:09:46,865 --> 00:09:48,345
-didn't she?
-Yes.

128
00:09:48,425 --> 00:09:50,905
She tricked those dispatch riders,
and they headed for Yunzhong.

129
00:09:58,265 --> 00:09:59,505
Good.

130
00:10:00,465 --> 00:10:02,505
Seems you are destined to die.

131
00:10:18,865 --> 00:10:20,545
This forest reeks of something foul.

132
00:10:21,305 --> 00:10:23,585
The traps and mechanisms
must be over a hundred.

133
00:10:25,065 --> 00:10:28,585
This is far too elaborate
for a mere stronghold of bandits.

134
00:10:30,665 --> 00:10:31,825
Are they truly trustworthy?

135
00:10:33,265 --> 00:10:34,505
I'm not sure.

136
00:10:34,585 --> 00:10:35,945
Then why did you insist on coming?

137
00:10:41,585 --> 00:10:42,825
Madam Ge wasn't lying.

138
00:10:43,505 --> 00:10:46,065
Her story matches perfectly
with what I knew of the past.

139
00:10:46,985 --> 00:10:51,265
It seems Cangmu Stronghold wasn't always
at odds with my father,

140
00:10:51,345 --> 00:10:52,705
despite what rumors say.

141
00:10:53,385 --> 00:10:55,065
Tie Ying is no fool.

142
00:10:55,145 --> 00:10:57,545
My tricks will only last
half a day at most.

143
00:10:58,185 --> 00:10:59,585
We are outnumbered.

144
00:10:59,665 --> 00:11:00,705
A head-on fight is not the best course.

145
00:11:01,305 --> 00:11:03,185
We'd better seek refuge
in Cangmu Stronghold

146
00:11:03,265 --> 00:11:05,465
and plan our next move
after scouting the truth.

147
00:11:07,705 --> 00:11:10,665
So, you're still gambling.

148
00:11:11,425 --> 00:11:13,865
I dared to risk
only because you stood by me.

149
00:11:29,945 --> 00:11:31,065
Don't get cocky.

150
00:11:31,785 --> 00:11:33,425
Last night, you were clearly defenseless,

151
00:11:34,145 --> 00:11:35,825
yet you still chose
to provoke the bandits.

152
00:11:36,945 --> 00:11:39,385
Do you realize,
if I'd been a moment later,

153
00:11:39,465 --> 00:11:40,905
you'd be a corpse by now?

154
00:11:41,425 --> 00:11:42,905
If they wanted me dead,

155
00:11:42,985 --> 00:11:46,105
they would have struck
when I exposed Madam Ge's disguise.

156
00:11:47,785 --> 00:11:48,985
Is that why you risked your life?

157
00:11:50,385 --> 00:11:54,625
Her taking men disguised
as dispatch riders to steal the dispatch

158
00:11:54,705 --> 00:11:58,425
isn't to hurt my father
but to uncover the truth.

159
00:11:58,945 --> 00:12:01,785
In other words, she truly is helping him.

160
00:12:02,905 --> 00:12:03,945
Aren't you afraid

161
00:12:04,465 --> 00:12:06,265
you've jumped out of the frying pan
and straight into the fire?

162
00:12:07,025 --> 00:12:11,425
Isn't that just what we do every day?

163
00:12:24,665 --> 00:12:26,185
CANGMU STRONGHOLD

164
00:12:26,265 --> 00:12:27,825
-Ge is back.
-Ge's returned.

165
00:12:27,905 --> 00:12:28,945
-Ge.
-Madam.

166
00:12:29,025 --> 00:12:30,065
-Madam is back.
-Ge.

167
00:12:31,105 --> 00:12:32,345
-Ge.
-Welcome back.

168
00:12:32,425 --> 00:12:33,345
Ge.

169
00:12:33,425 --> 00:12:34,385
Let me take that.

170
00:12:34,465 --> 00:12:35,625
Ge.

171
00:12:37,465 --> 00:12:38,385
Aunt.

172
00:12:39,745 --> 00:12:42,465
-Laosan, we have guests.
-Coming.

173
00:12:44,705 --> 00:12:47,385
This is my younger brother, Ge Laosan,
leader of Cangmu Stronghold.

174
00:12:48,145 --> 00:12:49,345
Greetings, Mr. Ge.

175
00:12:49,425 --> 00:12:50,905
‎GE LAOSAN, CANGMU STRONGHOLD

176
00:12:51,625 --> 00:12:52,585
Xiaoman.

177
00:12:52,665 --> 00:12:53,585
‎XIAOMAN, CANGMU STRONGHOLD

178
00:12:54,425 --> 00:12:55,345
Take a seat.

179
00:12:56,425 --> 00:12:58,025
Why'd you bring two strangers back?

180
00:13:00,105 --> 00:13:01,105
We need a place to lie low for a while.

181
00:13:01,185 --> 00:13:02,185
Lie low?

182
00:13:02,705 --> 00:13:05,305
How should I address you two?

183
00:13:05,905 --> 00:13:07,865
He's Jiu. I'm Fu.

184
00:13:08,465 --> 00:13:09,785
Fu.

185
00:13:10,305 --> 00:13:11,825
Good name.

186
00:13:12,465 --> 00:13:14,145
Sounds like good fortune.

187
00:13:17,105 --> 00:13:19,905
Madam Ge, there's something I need to ask.

188
00:13:19,985 --> 00:13:21,665
I know what it is.

189
00:13:22,265 --> 00:13:23,305
Don't worry.

190
00:13:23,825 --> 00:13:25,745
You saw it for yourselves on the way in.

191
00:13:26,385 --> 00:13:29,625
We are known as Cangmu Stronghold,
hidden deep within these woods.

192
00:13:30,265 --> 00:13:31,625
There's a saying down the mountain,

193
00:13:31,705 --> 00:13:34,305
"Once you go deep into Cangmu Forest,
there's no way out."

194
00:13:34,905 --> 00:13:38,025
This forest is vast and deep,
a fortress built by nature itself.

195
00:13:38,105 --> 00:13:40,265
And we have all those hidden mechanisms
and traps.

196
00:13:40,345 --> 00:13:43,865
With bamboo nets overhead
and vine-traps underfoot,

197
00:13:43,945 --> 00:13:45,465
all life is barred from entry,

198
00:13:45,545 --> 00:13:46,905
be it human or beast.

199
00:13:46,985 --> 00:13:49,825
Here, you're safer than anywhere outside.

200
00:13:50,545 --> 00:13:52,585
If this place is so secret,

201
00:13:53,345 --> 00:13:55,625
how could you trust us enough
to let us in?

202
00:13:56,625 --> 00:13:57,585
Aren't you afraid?

203
00:13:57,665 --> 00:13:59,945
We value fate above all.

204
00:14:00,025 --> 00:14:02,265
I've trusted you, so I won't question it.

205
00:14:06,265 --> 00:14:08,745
Xiaoman, see to our guests.

206
00:14:08,825 --> 00:14:11,785
Once things calm down out there,
you can resume your journey.

207
00:14:13,745 --> 00:14:14,585
My gratitude, ma'am.

208
00:14:16,465 --> 00:14:17,545
Apologies for the intrusion.

209
00:14:17,625 --> 00:14:19,785
No trouble at all.

210
00:14:20,505 --> 00:14:21,425
This way, please.

211
00:14:24,185 --> 00:14:26,585
Have a good rest.

212
00:14:31,545 --> 00:14:32,465
She…?

213
00:14:48,905 --> 00:14:50,185
Mr. Tie!

214
00:14:50,705 --> 00:14:51,785
Mr. Tie.

215
00:14:54,625 --> 00:14:56,065
Mr. Tie. Something's wrong.

216
00:14:56,145 --> 00:14:57,705
The dispatch riders we were pursuing,
along with the Grand Princess,

217
00:14:57,785 --> 00:15:00,385
have vanished without a trace
near Cangmu Stronghold.

218
00:15:01,265 --> 00:15:02,385
The men we dispatched in pursuit

219
00:15:02,465 --> 00:15:04,785
were all slain
by the bandits of the stronghold.

220
00:15:05,825 --> 00:15:07,065
Cangmu Stronghold?

221
00:15:08,145 --> 00:15:11,985
I promised His Highness
to bring back Chu Zhao's head.

222
00:15:13,745 --> 00:15:15,505
Hear my command.

223
00:15:15,585 --> 00:15:17,825
Pick up the pace
and march into Cangmu Forest.

224
00:15:17,905 --> 00:15:19,785
Leave no one alive.

225
00:15:19,865 --> 00:15:24,465
I'd like to see what these remnants think
they can do to shield her.

226
00:15:35,185 --> 00:15:39,105
They offered you shelter,
and now you're raiding their armory?

227
00:15:39,185 --> 00:15:40,385
Cangmu Forest is vast and deep.

228
00:15:40,465 --> 00:15:42,745
They seem hospitable enough,

229
00:15:42,825 --> 00:15:45,865
but how could we truly rest easy
without investigating first?

230
00:15:47,105 --> 00:15:47,945
I didn't realize,

231
00:15:48,025 --> 00:15:50,305
though new to the jianghu,
you would think further ahead than I.

232
00:15:52,105 --> 00:15:53,065
Look at this.

233
00:15:55,105 --> 00:15:56,425
Careful.

234
00:16:02,505 --> 00:16:03,625
Seven modifications to the mechanism.

235
00:16:03,705 --> 00:16:07,385
Range increased by two zhang,
with less recoil.

236
00:16:08,705 --> 00:16:11,305
These are modified crossbows
the frontier troops used

237
00:16:11,385 --> 00:16:12,505
against the Northern Desert.

238
00:16:13,705 --> 00:16:14,745
How do you know?

239
00:16:14,825 --> 00:16:16,225
Back when I was in the army,

240
00:16:16,305 --> 00:16:18,425
I modified over 200
of these crossbows for the General.

241
00:16:19,945 --> 00:16:22,425
Mu Mianhong was killed
by my father, after all.

242
00:16:23,185 --> 00:16:26,305
So why would her stronghold
have weapons from the frontier troops?

243
00:16:26,905 --> 00:16:27,865
It's not just that.

244
00:16:28,905 --> 00:16:30,465
While searching for you,

245
00:16:30,545 --> 00:16:32,225
I saved a dispatch rider
who had been kidnapped by Madam Ge.

246
00:16:33,305 --> 00:16:34,745
<i>The knots used to tie him up</i>

247
00:16:35,785 --> 00:16:37,705
<i>were standard frontier troop rigging.</i>

248
00:16:38,305 --> 00:16:39,985
You mean…?

249
00:16:40,065 --> 00:16:41,185
Perhaps

250
00:16:41,945 --> 00:16:44,385
your father wasn't here
to suppress bandits.

251
00:16:44,465 --> 00:16:45,985
What are you implying?

252
00:16:46,065 --> 00:16:48,785
-Are you suggesting my father…?
-Wait for me.

253
00:16:57,865 --> 00:16:58,865
I won't be long.

254
00:17:55,705 --> 00:17:56,825
Your Highness,

255
00:17:57,825 --> 00:17:59,265
this feels a little too personal.

256
00:18:01,425 --> 00:18:03,025
Back when I left the Capital,

257
00:18:03,105 --> 00:18:05,505
who was it that swore
to guard the imperial city for me?

258
00:18:12,385 --> 00:18:15,305
I know it's because you care about me.

259
00:18:18,385 --> 00:18:22,025
But Xie Yanfang wouldn't release you
without expecting something in return.

260
00:18:23,545 --> 00:18:24,785
What's the situation at court?

261
00:18:25,305 --> 00:18:28,025
He'll look after Yu.

262
00:18:28,985 --> 00:18:32,225
But he needs the Grand Princess Token
to keep Deng Yi on a leash.

263
00:18:34,665 --> 00:18:36,065
So I handed it over.

264
00:18:43,625 --> 00:18:44,705
Indeed.

265
00:18:45,745 --> 00:18:47,265
Your brother

266
00:18:47,785 --> 00:18:49,865
has never been one to show his hand
without a guaranteed win.

267
00:18:51,345 --> 00:18:52,625
If you're not in the Capital,

268
00:18:53,385 --> 00:18:56,225
he's the only one who can keep Yu safe.

269
00:19:01,745 --> 00:19:02,985
Your wounds have yet to heal.

270
00:19:03,065 --> 00:19:04,105
You need proper rest.

271
00:19:07,905 --> 00:19:09,025
Just get some sleep.

272
00:19:24,985 --> 00:19:28,945
They… only gave us one room?

273
00:19:34,065 --> 00:19:35,025
I insisted on this.

274
00:19:37,545 --> 00:19:39,105
With such grave injuries,

275
00:19:40,545 --> 00:19:42,105
you need to stay close to me.

276
00:19:43,025 --> 00:19:44,545
Or how am I supposed to protect you?

277
00:20:00,505 --> 00:20:01,905
And how will you protect me exactly?

278
00:20:23,025 --> 00:20:24,145
It's a cold night.

279
00:20:26,065 --> 00:20:27,425
Your wounds won't heal if you freeze.

280
00:20:32,665 --> 00:20:33,745
Keep warm.

281
00:20:48,745 --> 00:20:50,785
Are you out of your mind?

282
00:20:51,745 --> 00:20:55,025
You knew who she was
and you still brought her here?

283
00:21:08,185 --> 00:21:09,905
They're not to be trifled with.

284
00:21:11,065 --> 00:21:14,745
Xiao Xun's ambushes
always have a deeper kill.

285
00:21:15,665 --> 00:21:18,065
That guard at the gate
sent word in the White Wolf tongue,

286
00:21:19,185 --> 00:21:20,745
saying the pursuers
have all been eliminated.

287
00:21:21,665 --> 00:21:25,385
If they were with Xiao Xun,
why would they kill their own?

288
00:21:26,225 --> 00:21:27,705
I didn't know you could speak that tongue.

289
00:21:28,705 --> 00:21:31,345
My father taught me
when we were in the desert.

290
00:21:33,505 --> 00:21:39,385
No one knows that except him.

291
00:21:40,265 --> 00:21:41,905
But what if it's all just an act?

292
00:21:42,585 --> 00:21:44,785
Xiao Xun's men have no reason
to slaughter their own.

293
00:21:45,385 --> 00:21:48,665
Given how cautious Deng Yi is,

294
00:21:49,265 --> 00:21:52,065
he'd never trust a band of bandits
who still answer to their old master.

295
00:21:52,145 --> 00:21:53,225
He wouldn't trust them.

296
00:21:54,185 --> 00:21:56,625
And Xie Yanfang? Even less likely.

297
00:21:58,545 --> 00:22:01,465
Whether Madam Ge and the others respect
my father or fear him,

298
00:22:03,025 --> 00:22:04,185
at the very least,

299
00:22:05,785 --> 00:22:09,305
my father never bore them any ill will.

300
00:22:10,385 --> 00:22:14,585
I still find it hard to believe
they've suddenly turned into saints.

301
00:22:15,345 --> 00:22:19,345
Are you willing to take a gamble with me?

302
00:22:20,305 --> 00:22:21,785
What if we lose?

303
00:22:31,145 --> 00:22:33,145
At least on the road to the afterlife,

304
00:22:34,505 --> 00:22:35,665
you'll keep me company.

305
00:22:41,985 --> 00:22:42,905
TAIJI HALL

306
00:22:42,985 --> 00:22:46,225
Recently, our dispatch riders
were ambushed near the Beicao Post House.

307
00:22:46,305 --> 00:22:48,905
Investigations confirm that this was
the work of the Cangmu Stronghold.

308
00:22:48,985 --> 00:22:51,905
This is an absolute outrage.

309
00:22:51,985 --> 00:22:53,305
-Utterly preposterous.
-Indeed.

310
00:22:53,385 --> 00:22:55,985
Chu Ling's leniency
allowed these bandits to flourish.

311
00:22:56,065 --> 00:22:58,825
Now, the remnants of that stronghold
have the audacity

312
00:22:58,905 --> 00:23:01,825
to pose as our dispatch riders
to steal vital military intelligence.

313
00:23:02,425 --> 00:23:03,865
Your Majesty, I implore you

314
00:23:03,945 --> 00:23:05,585
to issue a decree for a full investigation

315
00:23:05,665 --> 00:23:07,185
and ensure that justice is served.

316
00:23:08,025 --> 00:23:10,625
General Chu marched against the bandits
on imperial command.

317
00:23:10,705 --> 00:23:13,665
When the bandit leader, Mu Mianhong,
took her life by leaping from the cliff,

318
00:23:13,745 --> 00:23:14,945
he refused to harm
even the women and children

319
00:23:15,025 --> 00:23:16,345
remaining in the stronghold.

320
00:23:16,865 --> 00:23:20,785
To think that such benevolence
is being wielded against him?

321
00:23:20,865 --> 00:23:22,025
Well…

322
00:23:22,665 --> 00:23:25,065
Your Majesty, an urgent report
has just arrived.

323
00:23:25,145 --> 00:23:26,865
The Northern Desert
dispatched an envoy to Yunzhong,

324
00:23:26,945 --> 00:23:28,825
only for General Chu
to execute him on the spot.

325
00:23:29,425 --> 00:23:32,025
Tensions between the two states
are already high.

326
00:23:32,105 --> 00:23:33,665
What are we to do now?

327
00:23:33,745 --> 00:23:36,825
Even in war,
one does not kill a messenger.

328
00:23:36,905 --> 00:23:40,145
This act will surely incite them
to take up arms.

329
00:23:40,225 --> 00:23:42,385
The charge of leniency toward bandits
might be overlooked,

330
00:23:42,465 --> 00:23:45,625
but inciting a war is unpardonable.

331
00:23:46,545 --> 00:23:49,065
First, they breached our frontier.

332
00:23:49,145 --> 00:23:51,705
Then, their envoy infiltrated
the General's tent

333
00:23:51,785 --> 00:23:53,785
with a secret letter at night.

334
00:23:54,425 --> 00:23:56,185
If that isn't espionage, then what is?

335
00:23:56,265 --> 00:23:57,985
Mr. Deng is correct.

336
00:23:58,745 --> 00:24:00,705
The General has commanded
the frontier troops for decades,

337
00:24:00,785 --> 00:24:01,825
with his defenses impregnable.

338
00:24:01,905 --> 00:24:03,745
If they nearly faltered last time,

339
00:24:03,825 --> 00:24:05,585
it must be because a spy
leaked our positions.

340
00:24:06,625 --> 00:24:09,785
Desperate times demand desperate measures.

341
00:24:10,385 --> 00:24:11,385
According to our laws,

342
00:24:11,465 --> 00:24:14,625
when a threat is imminent and unclear,
one may act first and report thereafter.

343
00:24:15,465 --> 00:24:17,185
So how can General Chu be blamed?

344
00:24:20,105 --> 00:24:22,985
Your Majesty, General Chu
is advanced in years.

345
00:24:23,585 --> 00:24:25,625
As the frontier defenses
have seen repeated breaches,

346
00:24:25,705 --> 00:24:27,865
I beg Your Majesty
to appoint another worthy general.

347
00:24:29,785 --> 00:24:31,945
These concerns are not without merit.

348
00:24:32,025 --> 00:24:35,225
As the Northern Desert stirs
with ambition, we must fortify

349
00:24:35,945 --> 00:24:39,105
the frontier in anticipation of conflict.

350
00:24:40,585 --> 00:24:42,465
As for the selection of a successor,

351
00:24:44,865 --> 00:24:46,785
it remains a matter
for His Majesty's judgment.

352
00:24:47,385 --> 00:24:49,745
The General has held Yunzhong
for 20 years.

353
00:24:49,825 --> 00:24:52,625
Each time the enemy dared to invade,
they were repelled in ignominious defeat.

354
00:24:53,745 --> 00:24:55,905
In your candidate list,

355
00:24:55,985 --> 00:24:59,545
how many can truly rival
his illustrious record?

356
00:25:00,145 --> 00:25:01,905
A commander of such stature
is not cultivated overnight.

357
00:25:01,985 --> 00:25:06,425
Yet, the security of the frontier
cannot be staked upon a single individual.

358
00:25:07,985 --> 00:25:09,385
Mr. Xie, please set your mind at rest.

359
00:25:09,465 --> 00:25:12,545
I shall confer with the ministers

360
00:25:12,625 --> 00:25:16,785
to select the most fitting candidate
for Yunzhong Prefecture

361
00:25:17,665 --> 00:25:19,625
to alleviate the General's burdens.

362
00:25:25,865 --> 00:25:29,105
<i>What a masterful move he's played.</i>

363
00:25:47,185 --> 00:25:48,105
This is…

364
00:25:49,305 --> 00:25:50,145
Sand Fox Whistle.

365
00:25:50,225 --> 00:25:51,505
That's right.

366
00:25:52,265 --> 00:25:54,185
This is a frontier troop alert
for cavalry raids.

367
00:25:56,425 --> 00:25:57,945
Stubborn, aren't you?

368
00:25:58,025 --> 00:25:59,025
BROTHERS IN ARMS, WISE IN DEED

369
00:25:59,105 --> 00:26:00,225
Talk.

370
00:26:00,785 --> 00:26:01,865
If you won't,

371
00:26:02,545 --> 00:26:05,705
I'll chop you to pieces
and feed you to the wolves in the hills.

372
00:26:05,785 --> 00:26:08,305
-Throw him to the wolves!
-Throw him to the wolves!

373
00:26:08,385 --> 00:26:09,425
Talk or not?

374
00:26:12,225 --> 00:26:13,345
What are you doing here?

375
00:26:14,265 --> 00:26:15,665
I'm in the middle of something.

376
00:26:15,745 --> 00:26:16,585
Don't mind me.

377
00:26:17,265 --> 00:26:18,505
Leave him to me.

378
00:26:27,705 --> 00:26:29,625
-That's pretty brutal.
-Indeed.

379
00:26:29,705 --> 00:26:31,385
-Listen to the scream.
-Right.

380
00:26:32,265 --> 00:26:33,465
What is he doing?

381
00:26:33,545 --> 00:26:36,385
That's brutal.

382
00:26:36,905 --> 00:26:38,865
Tell me about it!

383
00:26:38,945 --> 00:26:40,745
Brutal…

384
00:26:45,305 --> 00:26:47,265
Didn't see that coming. He's good.

385
00:26:49,825 --> 00:26:51,985
-Well?
-He talked.

386
00:26:52,585 --> 00:26:56,065
They entered Cangmu Forest yesterday
and located Cangmu Stronghold.

387
00:26:56,145 --> 00:26:58,145
Their men will arrive tonight.

388
00:26:58,225 --> 00:26:59,225
We should prepare in advance.

389
00:26:59,985 --> 00:27:01,465
I need to tell my sister.

390
00:27:30,185 --> 00:27:34,945
Did you learn those interrogation tricks
from my father's army?

391
00:27:36,865 --> 00:27:37,785
Not really.

392
00:27:39,505 --> 00:27:41,345
He advocated
for the humane treatment of captives.

393
00:27:42,145 --> 00:27:44,105
He'd never have used torture on them.

394
00:27:49,105 --> 00:27:50,185
Are you not afraid anymore?

395
00:27:50,945 --> 00:27:52,225
Why would I?

396
00:27:52,865 --> 00:27:54,665
I grew up in military camps.

397
00:27:54,745 --> 00:27:56,465
I've seen my share

398
00:27:57,225 --> 00:27:58,625
of slaughter and bloodshed.

399
00:28:06,985 --> 00:28:08,745
That is no blessing.

400
00:28:10,225 --> 00:28:11,385
Better to have never seen it at all.

401
00:28:17,505 --> 00:28:20,745
But in this life, who truly has a choice?

402
00:28:22,145 --> 00:28:25,185
I have no desire to kill,
yet they come for my life.

403
00:28:26,545 --> 00:28:32,985
I told you I kill
just so I can stay alive.

404
00:28:35,105 --> 00:28:38,385
I want to live to see my father again.

405
00:28:39,745 --> 00:28:40,625
I will do the killing for you.

406
00:28:46,825 --> 00:28:48,425
Hey. The ones after them

407
00:28:48,505 --> 00:28:51,625
belong to Xiao Xun,
heir to the Lord of Xiaonan.

408
00:28:52,585 --> 00:28:54,065
A humble meal

409
00:28:55,305 --> 00:28:56,865
in a humble place.

410
00:28:59,305 --> 00:29:00,865
I hope Your Highness can forgive me.

411
00:29:21,105 --> 00:29:22,785
You are the Grand Princess?

412
00:29:23,705 --> 00:29:26,865
No. You were supposed to marry
the heir to the Lord of Xiaonan.

413
00:29:28,785 --> 00:29:29,945
So you eloped with this man?

414
00:29:39,265 --> 00:29:40,585
Xiao Xun deceived me.

415
00:29:41,465 --> 00:29:42,985
Everything he wanted,

416
00:29:43,065 --> 00:29:46,145
from the very start,
was my father's command over the army.

417
00:29:47,385 --> 00:29:48,745
But I won't let him have it.

418
00:29:51,065 --> 00:29:52,225
Never ever.

419
00:29:52,985 --> 00:29:54,865
You're Chu Ling's daughter.

420
00:29:55,705 --> 00:29:58,105
Did he ever tell you who your mother was?

421
00:30:06,625 --> 00:30:09,305
Mr. Ge, you take quite an interest
in Yunzhong Prefecture.

422
00:30:10,345 --> 00:30:12,585
You even know every detail
of my betrothal.

423
00:30:13,265 --> 00:30:18,585
No wonder this stronghold
bears the marks of frontier troops.

424
00:30:28,785 --> 00:30:32,585
Since we're speaking so frankly,
ma'am, you might as well tell the truth.

425
00:30:33,105 --> 00:30:35,785
What really happened when my father went

426
00:30:37,305 --> 00:30:39,065
to Cangmu Stronghold?

427
00:30:39,945 --> 00:30:41,465
Nothing much.

428
00:30:42,505 --> 00:30:47,145
It's just
that General Chu killed our former leader.

429
00:30:47,825 --> 00:30:49,425
Then why do you still care
about him so much?

430
00:30:50,585 --> 00:30:53,825
Don't you want to avenge your leader?

431
00:31:01,065 --> 00:31:05,065
Back then, word got out
that we were raiding the frontier,

432
00:31:05,145 --> 00:31:06,945
so General Chu came to eradicate us.

433
00:31:07,745 --> 00:31:10,825
But after killing the former leader,
he realized it was all a misunderstanding.

434
00:31:11,985 --> 00:31:14,025
So he stepped in to resettle
the rest of us.

435
00:31:14,625 --> 00:31:16,105
Everything you see now

436
00:31:16,185 --> 00:31:19,705
is just your father's guilt
and his way of making amends.

437
00:31:21,225 --> 00:31:22,625
-But…
-The debt has been settled.

438
00:31:24,025 --> 00:31:25,465
There's no point bringing it up anymore.

439
00:31:29,185 --> 00:31:30,625
You've had a long journey.

440
00:31:30,705 --> 00:31:31,745
Why don't you try to get some rest?

441
00:31:32,465 --> 00:31:33,865
I'm right here if you need anything.

442
00:31:51,825 --> 00:31:53,545
They aren't like ordinary bandits.

443
00:31:54,425 --> 00:31:58,265
Their story about the General's campaign,
how he supposedly killed the innocents,

444
00:31:58,905 --> 00:32:00,505
is rather flimsy.

445
00:32:02,305 --> 00:32:04,105
Largely fiction, with a grain of truth.

446
00:32:06,425 --> 00:32:09,505
But I do believe my father
genuinely wanted to protect this place.

447
00:32:10,465 --> 00:32:15,105
And I'm certain they mean no harm to us.

448
00:32:15,705 --> 00:32:17,185
As for the rest…

449
00:32:17,705 --> 00:32:19,345
Everyone has secrets.

450
00:32:20,185 --> 00:32:24,025
When they'll finally come to light,
that's just a matter of fate.

451
00:32:30,945 --> 00:32:32,185
Wangcheng is just ahead.

452
00:32:32,265 --> 00:32:35,185
Past it lies Yunzhong Prefecture.

453
00:32:37,065 --> 00:32:38,785
Once we deal with Xiao Xun's men,

454
00:32:41,905 --> 00:32:43,185
you'll finally see your father.

455
00:32:45,545 --> 00:32:46,545
I know.

456
00:32:48,145 --> 00:32:49,225
I know this road

457
00:32:51,265 --> 00:32:52,505
all too well.

458
00:32:58,985 --> 00:33:00,025
<i>Back then,</i>

459
00:33:01,265 --> 00:33:03,105
<i>this was the exact path I took</i>

460
00:33:04,545 --> 00:33:05,945
<i>to be away from my father,</i>

461
00:33:08,065 --> 00:33:09,465
<i>Yunzhong Prefecture,</i>

462
00:33:10,985 --> 00:33:13,025
<i>and everything that held me dear,</i>

463
00:33:13,105 --> 00:33:15,025
<i>only to fall</i>

464
00:33:16,545 --> 00:33:18,585
<i>into the mire of eternal doom.</i>

465
00:33:43,465 --> 00:33:44,305
Jiu.

466
00:33:46,545 --> 00:33:48,745
If we had a second chance at life,

467
00:33:50,345 --> 00:33:52,465
would anything actually change?

468
00:34:01,865 --> 00:34:02,865
A second chance

469
00:34:04,745 --> 00:34:06,145
<i>at life…</i>

470
00:34:06,225 --> 00:34:06,865
GRACE AND BENEVOLENCE

471
00:34:09,264 --> 00:34:11,905
<i>‎Jiu, from now on, you have</i>
<i>‎a home here at Xie Residence.</i>

472
00:34:12,824 --> 00:34:14,744
<i>‎Mother!</i>

473
00:34:35,185 --> 00:34:36,344
Perhaps it wouldn't change a thing.

474
00:34:38,264 --> 00:34:39,545
But for me,

475
00:34:41,065 --> 00:34:42,465
things are already different.

476
00:34:45,824 --> 00:34:49,945
Remember that dream I told you about?

477
00:34:51,545 --> 00:34:53,025
<i>At the very end,</i>

478
00:34:54,225 --> 00:34:57,425
<i>someone killed Xiao Xun for me.</i>

479
00:34:59,945 --> 00:35:01,785
<i>Do you know who it was?</i>

480
00:35:03,945 --> 00:35:05,305
It was you.

481
00:35:13,745 --> 00:35:18,225
You killed him and avenged my family.

482
00:35:22,465 --> 00:35:23,705
But this time,

483
00:35:26,585 --> 00:35:28,225
I have to do it myself.

484
00:35:29,025 --> 00:35:31,545
Though fear may still echo in my chest,

485
00:35:33,265 --> 00:35:35,865
and a crumbling cliff awaits my next step,

486
00:35:36,465 --> 00:35:37,385
nothing in this world

487
00:35:40,425 --> 00:35:41,945
will hold me back.

488
00:36:18,585 --> 00:36:20,265
Whatever you fear in the days to come,

489
00:36:22,105 --> 00:36:26,065
whatever that dream may be, real or not,

490
00:36:28,025 --> 00:36:29,025
face it,

491
00:36:30,785 --> 00:36:31,745
grasp it,

492
00:36:33,185 --> 00:36:34,385
and conquer it.

493
00:36:40,945 --> 00:36:42,625
And the fear will leave you.

494
00:36:43,865 --> 00:36:45,025
I'm not terrified.

495
00:36:47,425 --> 00:36:48,865
My father and I

496
00:36:50,785 --> 00:36:52,585
will survive.

